The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 October is 83,516 (9,625.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 October, there were 2,851 new confirmed cases (328.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 October, there were 2,435 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 17% (416 extra cases).
